source: crates/daemon/tests/cli_help.rs
expression: stdout
---
Terminal email client (pronounced "Mixer")

Usage: mxr [COMMAND]

Commands:
  daemon              Start the daemon explicitly
  restart             Restart the daemon with the current binary
  search              Search messages
  count               Count matching messages
  cat                 Display a message. Pass a positional ID, pipe IDs on stdin, or resolve a list with `--search QUERY` (then `--first` for the most recent match or `--limit N` for the top N)
  thread              Display a thread. Pass a positional ID, pipe IDs on stdin, or resolve a list with `--search QUERY` (deduplicated by thread)
  export              Export a thread or matching search results
  headers             Show message headers. Pass a positional ID, pipe IDs on stdin, or resolve a list with `--search QUERY`
  saved               Manage saved searches
  replies             Manage the reply-later queue
  summarize           Summarise an email thread using the configured LLM (Ollama, LM Studio, OpenAI, etc.). Requires `[llm] enabled = true` in config. Pass a positional thread ID or use `--search QUERY` plus `--first` (most recent match) or `--limit N` to summarize multiple threads in one go. Multi-summary output is separated by `--- THREAD_ID ---`
  draft-assist        Generate a draft reply for a thread, grounded on the thread context plus the user's instruction. Output goes to stdout — pipe it into `$EDITOR` or your scratch buffer. Never auto-sends. Two equivalent forms:
  draft               Draft a new email or refine an existing local draft with LLM assistance
  setup               First-run setup wizard for demo, Gmail, or IMAP/SMTP
  demo                Launch an isolated, realistic demo inbox without touching your real config
  screener            Triage unknown senders: classify them as allow / deny / feed / paper-trail. Local-only consent metadata; never roundtrips to the provider
  sender              Show per-sender relationship aggregates: volume, response cadence, open threads. The unfair advantage of having local SQLite — every other email tool reasons over messages, not people
  profile             Show or rebuild the inspectable relationship profile for a contact
  expert              Find people who have answered similar questions before. Either give the message id of the question OR a free-text query; the daemon ranks answerers (not askers)
  suggest-recipients  Suggest "maybe include" Cc recipients for a draft. Excludes addresses already on the draft and never reveals Bcc'd addresses from prior threads
  whois               Explain an entity (email or term) using local evidence
  briefing            Render a thread or recipient briefing
  cadence             Manage the cadence watchlist
  send-time           Show the recipient's typical reply-time bucket
  decisions           List or rebuild the citation-backed decision log
  ask                 Ask a question against the local archive. Returns a citation- validated answer; the daemon rejects LLM citations that point to messages outside the retrieved set
  owed                List threads where the user owes a reply, ranked by how overdue they are relative to the recipient's typical cadence
  commitments         List or resolve relationship commitments
  voice               Show or rebuild the account-level user voice profile
  humanize            Score or rewrite text using the deterministic humanizer gate
  snippets            Manage compose snippets (`;name` expansions)
  signatures          Manage outgoing compose signatures
  remind              Set or cancel a follow-up reminder on an outbound message. Reminders fire if no reply has arrived by the given time — surfacing the message back to the user as a follow-up
  semantic            Manage semantic search profiles and indexing
  llm                 Inspect local/cloud LLM provider status
  subscriptions       List senders with unsubscribe support
  senders             List top inbound senders by message volume
  storage             Roll up disk consumption by sender, mimetype, or label
  contacts            Surface relationship analytics from the materialized contacts table
  wrapped             Year-in-review summary: volume, time patterns, top contacts, reply discipline, storage, newsletters, superlatives. Like Spotify Wrapped but for your inbox
  response-time       Reply-latency percentiles (clock + business-hours) per direction
  stale               List stale threads waiting for a reply (mine = my turn, theirs = theirs)
  sync                Trigger or query sync
  status              Show daemon status
  web                 Start or reopen the local HTTP/WebSocket bridge and open the web app in the default browser. Runs detached by default; use `mxr web stop` to stop the detached bridge
  events              Watch daemon events
  activity            Browse the local user-activity log (the git-reflog for your inbox). Strictly local: never transmitted off-device. See `mxr activity --help`
  history             Show persisted event history
  notify              Unread summary for status bars
  logs                View daemon logs
  reset               Destroy local mxr runtime state after stopping the daemon. Preserves config.toml and credentials by default. Use --including-config to also delete config.toml. Destructive; use --dry-run to preview
  burn                Destroy local mxr runtime state after stopping the daemon. Alias for `mxr reset --hard`. Preserves config.toml and credentials by default. Use --including-config to also delete config.toml. Destructive; use --dry-run to preview
  bug-report          Generate a sanitized diagnostic bundle
  accounts            Manage accounts
  doctor              Run diagnostics
  labels              Manage labels
  rules               Manage rules
  compose             Compose a new email
  reply               Reply to a message
  reply-all           Reply to all recipients
  forward             Forward a message
  drafts              Manage drafts: list (default), recover orphaned in-flight sends, resume one for retry, or discard recovered drafts
  send                Send a draft by ID
  unsend              Cancel a previously-scheduled send. The draft itself is preserved
  archive             Archive a message (remove from inbox)
  read-archive        Mark message as read and archive it
  trash               Move message to trash
  spam                Report message as spam
  star                Star a message
  unstar              Unstar a message
  read                Mark message as read
  unread              Mark message as unread
  label               Apply a label to a message
  unlabel             Remove a label from a message
  move                Move message to a label/folder
  undo                Undo a recent destructive mutation by its id (~60s window). The mutation id is printed by `archive`, `trash`, `spam`, `mark-read`, and `read-archive`; copy it from there
  snooze              Snooze a message until a specified time
  unsnooze            Unsnooze a message
  snoozed             List snoozed messages
  unsubscribe         Unsubscribe from a mailing list
  open                Open message in browser. Pass a positional ID or `--search QUERY` (with `--first` for the latest match, or `--limit N` plus `--yes` to open many tabs at once)
  attachments         Manage message attachments
  config              Configuration management
  version             Show version
  completions         Generate shell completions
  help                Print this message or the help of the given subcommand(s)

Options:
  -h, --help     Print help
  -V, --version  Print version
